<para id="import-auto-id3586799">The minus sign indicates the average velocity is also toward the rear of the plane. </para>
    <para id="import-auto-id4125081">The average velocity of an object does not tell us anything about what happens to it between the starting point and ending point, however. For example, we cannot tell from average velocity whether the airplane passenger stops momentarily or backs up before he goes to the back of the plane. To get more details, we must consider smaller segments of the trip over smaller time intervals. </para>
    
